               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus” (fols. 3ra-73ra)
 I-1)
                     ʾƎsaggǝd la-malakotǝka... “I worship Thy Godhead…” (fols. 3ra-5v l.4)
 I-2)
                     Introduction (fols. 5ra-13rb) 
 - On John the Evangelist as the author of
                     the book; on the creation and the fall of the angels (fols. 5ra-9ra) 
 -
                     Story of the family of Adam (fols. 9ra-13rb)
 I-3) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus
                     “Miracles of Jesus”: 34 miracles (fols. 13rb-73ra).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The miracles are not numbered. They are introduced with the words mǝʿrāf
                        “chapter”, taʾammǝr “miracle”, täʾamrihu “his miracle”, nägär
                        “speech”.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
